aboutSections.name: About
aboutSections.description: Juicy burger. Sweet charred onion. Creamy dijon aioli. Toasted garlic butter buns. Crispy frites. No, this is not a copy-and-paste of le menu from that fancy bistro downtown. Its what you (yes YOU!) are capable of making in 45 minutes or less. So put on your (cleanest) apron, cue up your favorite tunes, and pop open a bottle of wine. Now all you need is someone to bring you a chocolate souffl.

aboutSections.name: The Exciting Part
aboutSections.description: When I think of a burger...I think of a delicious juicy patty, griddled to perfection, served with the most amazing sauce and fries that are bloody delicious.

steps.description: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut potatoes into -inchthick wedges. Trim and peel onion; slice into four -inch-thick rounds (eight rounds for 4 servings). Finely chop remaining onion until you have about  cup ( cup for 4). Peel and finely chop garlic. Halve buns.
Toss potatoes on a baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast until golden brown and tender, 20-25 minutes. Remove from sheet.

Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, mustard, and a pinch of garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Form beef into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each a bit wider than a burger bun. Season all over with salt and pepper; set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Turn off heat; stir cooked onion into mayonnaise mixture. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add onion rounds and cook until deeply browned and tender, 2-3 minutes per side. Transfer to a plate.
Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked to desired doneness, 3-5 minutes per side.

While patties cook, place remaining garlic and 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small microwave-safe bowl; microwave until melted, 30 seconds. Brush onto cut sides of buns and place cut sides up on baking sheet used for potatoes. Toast in oven until golden, 3-5 minutes. Fill toasted buns with patties, aioli, and griddled onion rounds. Serve with potatoes and, if youve got some on hand, ketchup on the side for dipping.
